HEADWORD: Sterlet
<hw>Ster"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>sterliade</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small sturgeon
(<spn>Acipenser ruthenus</spn>) found in the Caspian Sea and its rivers,
and highly esteemed for its flavor. The finest caviar is made from its
roe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sterling</ent>⟦br⟧
